 {"id":"bd-10i.4.1","title":"Implement BufferDiff with row-major scan","description":"# Implement BufferDiff with row-major scan

## Objective
Implement the diff engine that computes changed cells between two buffers efficiently.

## Why Diffing Matters
The fundamental theorem of terminal UI: produce the minimal byte stream to transform current grid to desired grid. Diffing identifies what actually changed so we don't re-emit unchanged cells.

## Technical Design

### Structure
pub struct BufferDiff {
    changes: Vec<(u16, u16)>,  // (x, y) of changed cells
}

### Algorithm
Row-major scan for cache efficiency:
1. Iterate y from 0 to height
2. Iterate x from 0 to width
3. Compare old[x,y] with new[x,y] using bits_eq
4. Record position if different

Row-major ensures sequential memory access:
- Cells are stored row-by-row
- Prefetcher can anticipate next access
- 4 cells per cache line means 4 comparisons per line load

### Implementation
impl BufferDiff {
    pub fn compute(old: &Buffer, new: &Buffer) -> Self {
        debug_assert_eq!(old.width(), new.width());
        debug_assert_eq!(old.height(), new.height());

        let mut changes = Vec::new();
        let width = old.width();
        let height = old.height();

        // Row-major scan for cache efficiency
        for y in 0..height {
            for x in 0..width {
                let old_cell = old.get_unchecked(x, y);
                let new_cell = new.get_unchecked(x, y);
                if !old_cell.bits_eq(new_cell) {
                    changes.push((x, y));
                }
            }
        }

        Self { changes }
    }

    pub fn len(&self) -> usize {
        self.changes.len()
    }

    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool {
        self.changes.is_empty()
    }

    pub fn changes(&self) -> &[(u16, u16)] {
        &self.changes
    }
}

### ChangeRun (for efficient emission)
Convert point changes into contiguous runs:

pub struct ChangeRun {
    pub y: u16,    // Row
    pub x0: u16,   // Start column
    pub x1: u16,   // End column (inclusive)
}

impl BufferDiff {
    pub fn runs(&self, _width: u16) -> Vec<ChangeRun> {
        // Sort by (y, x) - already sorted from scan
        // Coalesce consecutive x positions on same row

        let mut runs = Vec::new();
        if self.changes.is_empty() { return runs; }

        let mut sorted = self.changes.clone();
        sorted.sort_by_key(|(x, y)| (*y, *x));

        let mut i = 0;
        while i < sorted.len() {
            let (x0, y) = sorted[i];
            let mut x1 = x0;
            i += 1;

            // Coalesce consecutive x
            while i < sorted.len() {
                let (x, yy) = sorted[i];
                if yy != y || x != x1 + 1 { break; }
                x1 = x;
                i += 1;
            }

            runs.push(ChangeRun { y, x0, x1 });
        }

        runs
    }
}

## Performance Target
- 80x24, full diff: < 500us
- Typical 5% change: proportionally faster

## Tests Required
- [ ] Empty diff when buffers identical
- [ ] Single cell change detected
- [ ] Multiple scattered changes detected
- [ ] runs() coalesces adjacent cells
- [ ] runs() handles gaps correctly
- [ ] Performance meets target

