## Objective
Implement robust terminal input parsing with DoS protection.

## Parser States
enum ParserState {
    Ground,    // Normal character input
    Escape,    // After ESC
    Csi,       // After ESC [
    CsiParam,  // Collecting CSI parameters
    Osc,       // After ESC ]
    Dcs,       // After ESC P
    Ss3,       // After ESC O
}

## Transitions
Ground:
  ESC (0x1B) -> Escape
  0x00 -> Key(Null, Ctrl)
  0x01-0x1A -> Key(Ctrl+A..Z)
  0x7F -> Key(Backspace)
  0x80+ -> UTF-8 sequence
  other -> Key(Char)

Escape:
  [ -> Csi
  O -> Ss3
  ] -> Osc
  P -> Dcs
  other -> Key(Alt+char) + Ground

Csi:
  0-9;:<=>? -> CsiParam
  A-Za-z~ -> parse + Ground

CsiParam:
  0-9;: -> stay
  A-Za-z~Mm -> parse + Ground

Ss3:
  A-S -> function key + Ground

Osc:
  BEL (0x07) -> complete + Ground
  ESC \\ -> complete + Ground

## DoS Protection Limits
const MAX_CSI_LEN: usize = 256;   // Prevent CSI bomb
const MAX_OSC_LEN: usize = 4096;
const MAX_DCS_LEN: usize = 4096;
const MAX_PASTE_LEN: usize = 1024 * 1024;  // 1MB

If limit exceeded: abandon sequence, return to Ground.

## Special Sequences

### Bracketed Paste
CSI 200 ~ -> start paste mode
CSI 201 ~ -> end paste mode, emit Paste event

### Focus Events
CSI I -> Focus(true)
CSI O -> Focus(false)

### SGR Mouse (1006)
CSI < params M -> mouse down
CSI < params m -> mouse up
params: button ; x ; y

### Arrow Keys
CSI A -> Up
CSI B -> Down
CSI C -> Right
CSI D -> Left

### Function Keys
Ss3 P -> F1
Ss3 Q -> F2
etc.

CSI 15 ~ -> F5
CSI 17 ~ -> F6
etc.

## Implementation
pub struct InputParser {
    state: ParserState,
    buffer: Vec<u8>,
    paste_buffer: Vec<u8>,
    in_paste: bool,
    // Limits
    max_csi_len: usize,
    max_osc_len: usize,
    max_paste_len: usize,
}

impl InputParser {
    pub fn new() -> Self { ... }

    pub fn parse(&mut self, input: &[u8]) -> Vec<Event> {
        let mut events = Vec::new();
        for &byte in input {
            if let Some(event) = self.process_byte(byte) {
                events.push(event);
            }
        }
        events
    }
}

